  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad-\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dba-\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0db1\u0daf-\u0db1\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0daf-\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db8-\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba-\u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dd6\u0dbd-\u0dc3\u0dc4-\u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dd6\u0dbd-\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca/11-395793",
  "time_ut": 1658917593,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dba \u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0db1\u0daf \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dd2\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0daf \u0db8\u0dd9\u0db8 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba \u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dd6\u0dbd \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dd6\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Legitimate or not, this rule is a legal and constitutional rule",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Wimal Weerawansa, Member of Parliament representing the independent group, said that whether the present regime has legitimacy in the society or not, this regime is a legal and constitutional regime, and the country is governed by those rulers even if the people do not like it.",
        "Joining the debate held in Parliament today (27th) on the publication of hadiths, he said that the current struggle is to overthrow the state, and such statements are made to protect the state and not to get ministerial positions from President Ranil Wickramasinghe.",
        "Mr. Wimal Weerawansa, Member of Parliament, who further commented there,",
        "I don't think that there is enough good behavior in the society for the control that has been established. But this rule is a legitimate rule whether there is a certain amount of legitimacy or not. Constitutional governance. Whether we like it or not, that regime is ruling this country today. The former president resigned peacefully. Now this battle started with Gota Go Home. There was some approval in the society for saying Gota Go Home because of the oppressive situation and when they did not see any quick solutions. We thought it would end after Gota went home. Not so now.",
        "Now send another person home who will come on the 9th. When he goes home, Dinesh Siddaveili will become the president. This is a mess. Gota Go Home, Ranil Go Home, Dinesh Go Home. It's easier to say who you want. Let's make him president to avoid this trouble. Doesn't this country need to breathe in peace? Go home when told to go. Even now, this country will not be allowed to fight to get out of this economic crisis? We have criticisms of this regime. There are areas where we cannot agree. I will never understand the impulse of hundreds of thousands of people. To understand, here is the overthrow of the state. It cannot be allowed. Whether I am in the opposition or in the government, I cannot ask to allow it. I don't want Ranil Wickramasinghe to be a minister. I want my kingdom. He mentioned that we should have our state when we recover from the economic crisis."
      ],
